    How to unf*ck your life Paperback March 13, 2025

    by Christopher Serpico (Author)
    5.0 5.0 out of 5 stars (1)

    This book is a battle cry for men ready to take charge of their lives. It's not about complaining, making excuses, or waiting for a handout-it's about building yourself into a man who commands respect, earns his place, and leaves a lasting legacy.

    We'll tackle self-deception, toxic relationships, addiction, and the harsh truths about the world. Whether you're battling substance abuse, numbing yourself with distractions, or stuck in self-destructive cycles, you'll learn how to break free and rebuild from rock bottom. You'll learn to handle confrontation like a man, walk away from weak influences, and embrace the discipline it takes to succeed.

    We'll talk about strength-not just physical, but mental and moral. Are you a good man, or just harmless? Do you stand for something, or do you just exist? You'll learn to stop chasing validation, avoid the traps of weak-minded thinking, and understand the real difference between dreams and goals.

    Above all, this book is about action. It's about reclaiming your purpose, handling depression and anxiety like a warrior, and becoming irreplaceable in a world that values men for what they do, not what they are. It's about breaking free from addiction-not just to substances, but to comfort, weakness, and excuses.

    If you're tired of feeling lost, stuck, or overlooked-this is your blueprint to transformation. It won't be easy, but nothing worth having ever is.

      Editorial Reviews

      About the Author

      Christopher Serpico is a man who has lived, fought, and clawed his way back from the edge. Born in the Mississippi Delta and hardened in the streets of Chicago, he's seen the dark side of life-gangs, addiction, violence, and near-death experiences. But instead of letting it define him, he used it as fuel to rebuild himself from the ground up.

      After surviving end-stage liver failure, he turned his pain into purpose, embracing discipline, self-respect, and an unbreakable mindset. Now a successful entrepreneur, devoted husband, and father, he spends his days running his eBay business, lifting weights, and passing hard-earned wisdom to those ready to hear it.

      Raw, unfiltered, and brutally honest, his words aren't for the weak. They're for men ready to unf*ck their lives and reclaim their power.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.
